77#ifdef CGAME
78#define MEM_POOL_SIZE 128 * 1024
79#else
80#define MEM_POOL_SIZE 1024 * 1024
81#endif
82
83static char memoryPool[MEM_POOL_SIZE];
84static int allocPoint, outOfMemory;
85
86
87/*
88===============
89UI_Alloc
90===============
91*/
92void *UI_Alloc( int size ) {
93 char *p;
94
95 if ( allocPoint + size > MEM_POOL_SIZE ) {
96 outOfMemory = qtrue;
97 if (DC->Print) {
98 DC->Print("UI_Alloc: Failure. Out of memory!\n");
99 }
100 //DC->trap_Print(S_COLOR_YELLOW"WARNING: UI Out of Memory!\n");
101 return NULL;
102 }
103
104 p = &memoryPool[allocPoint];
105
106 allocPoint += ( size + 15 ) & ~15;
107
108 return p;
109}

112===============
113UI_InitMemory

115*/
116void UI_InitMemory( void ) {
117 allocPoint = 0;
118 outOfMemory = qfalse;
119}
120
121qboolean UI_OutOfMemory( void ) {
122 return outOfMemory;
123}

129#define HASH_TABLE_SIZE 2048
130/*
131================
132return a hash value for the string
133================
134*/
135static unsigned hashForString(const char *str) {
136 int i;
137 unsigned hash;
138 char letter;
139
140 hash = 0;
141 i = 0;
142 while (str[i] != '\0') {
143 letter = tolower(str[i]);
144 hash+=(unsigned)(letter)*(i+119);
145 i++;
146 }
147 hash &= (HASH_TABLE_SIZE-1);
148 return hash;
149}
150
151typedef struct stringDef_s {
152 struct stringDef_s *next;
153 const char *str;
154} stringDef_t;
155
156static int strPoolIndex = 0;
157static char strPool[STRING_POOL_SIZE];
158
159static int strHandleCount = 0;
160static stringDef_t *strHandle[HASH_TABLE_SIZE];
161
162
163const char *String_Alloc(const char *p) {
164 int len;
165 unsigned hash;
166 stringDef_t *str, *last;
167 static const char *staticNULL = "";
168
169 if (p == NULL) {
170 return NULL;
171 }
172
173 if (*p == 0) {
174 return staticNULL;
175 }
176
177 hash = hashForString(p);
178
179 str = strHandle[hash];
180 while (str) {
181 if (strcmp(p, str->str) == 0) {
182 return str->str;
183 }
184 str = str->next;
185 }
186
187 len = strlen(p);
188 if (len + strPoolIndex + 1 < STRING_POOL_SIZE) {
189 int ph = strPoolIndex;
190 strcpy(&strPool[strPoolIndex], p);
191 strPoolIndex += len + 1;
192
193 str = strHandle[hash];
194 last = str;
195 while (str && str->next) {
196 last = str;
197 str = str->next;
198 }
199
200 str = UI_Alloc(sizeof(stringDef_t));
201 str->next = NULL;
202 str->str = &strPool[ph];
203 if (last) {
204 last->next = str;
205 } else {
206 strHandle[hash] = str;
207 }
208 return &strPool[ph];
209 }
210 return NULL;
211}
212
213void String_Report(void) {
214 float f;
215 Com_Printf("Memory/String Pool Info\n");
216 Com_Printf("----------------\n");
217 f = strPoolIndex;
218 f /= STRING_POOL_SIZE;
219 f *= 100;
220 Com_Printf("String Pool is %.1f%% full, %i bytes out of %i used.\n", f, strPoolIndex, STRING_POOL_SIZE);
221 f = allocPoint;
222 f /= MEM_POOL_SIZE;
223 f *= 100;
224 Com_Printf("Memory Pool is %.1f%% full, %i bytes out of %i used.\n", f, allocPoint, MEM_POOL_SIZE);
225}

295/*
296=================
297LerpColor
298=================
299*/
300void LerpColor(vec4_t a, vec4_t b, vec4_t c, float t)
301{
302 int i;
303
304 // lerp and clamp each component
305 for (i=0; i<4; i++)
306 {
307 c[i] = a[i] + t*(b[i]-a[i]);
308 if (c[i] < 0)
309 c[i] = 0;
310 else if (c[i] > 1.0)
311 c[i] = 1.0;
312 }
313}

315/*
316=================
317Float_Parse
318=================
319*/
320qboolean Float_Parse(char **p, float *f) {
321 char *token;
322 token = COM_ParseExt(p, qfalse);
323 if (token && token[0] != 0) {
324 *f = atof(token);
325 return qtrue;
326 } else {
327 return qfalse;
328 }
329}
330
331/*
332=================
333PC_Float_Parse
334=================
335*/
336qboolean PC_Float_Parse(int handle, float *f) {
337 pc_token_t token;
338 int negative = qfalse;
339
340 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
341 return qfalse;
342 if (token.string[0] == '-') {
343 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
344 return qfalse;
345 negative = qtrue;
346 }
347 if (token.type != TT_NUMBER) {
348 PC_SourceError(handle, "expected float but found %s", token.string);
349 return qfalse;
350 }
351 if (negative)
352 *f = -token.floatvalue;
353 else
354 *f = token.floatvalue;
355 return qtrue;
356}

358/*
359=================
360Color_Parse
361=================
362*/
363qboolean Color_Parse(char **p, vec4_t *c) {
364 int i;
365 float f;
366
367 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
368 if (!Float_Parse(p, &f)) {
369 return qfalse;
370 }
371 (*c)[i] = f;
372 }
373 return qtrue;
374}

411/*
412=================
413PC_Int_Parse
414=================
415*/
416qboolean PC_Int_Parse(int handle, int *i) {
417 pc_token_t token;
418 int negative = qfalse;
419
420 if (!i)
421 return qfalse;
422 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
423 return qfalse;
424 if (token.string[0] == '-') {
425 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
426 return qfalse;
427 negative = qtrue;
428 }
429 if (token.type != TT_NUMBER) {
430 PC_SourceError(handle, "expected integer but found %s", token.string);
431 return qfalse;
432 }
433 *i = token.intvalue;
434 if (negative)
435 *i = - *i;
436 return qtrue;
437}

480qboolean String_Parse(char **p, const char **out) {

486 return qtrue;

491/*
492=================
493PC_String_Parse
494=================
495*/
496qboolean PC_String_Parse(int handle, const char **out) {
497 pc_token_t token;
498
499 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
500 return qfalse;
501
502 *(out) = String_Alloc(token.string);
503 return qtrue;
504}
505
506/*
507=================
508PC_Script_Parse
509=================
510*/
511qboolean PC_Script_Parse(int handle, const char **out) {
512 char script[1024];
513 pc_token_t token;
514
515 memset(script, 0, sizeof(script));
516 // scripts start with { and have ; separated command lists.. commands are command, arg..
517 // basically we want everything between the { } as it will be interpreted at run time
518
519 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
520 return qfalse;
521 if (Q_stricmp(token.string, "{") != 0) {
522 return qfalse;
523 }
524
525 while ( 1 ) {
526 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
527 return qfalse;
528
529 if (Q_stricmp(token.string, "}") == 0) {
530 *out = String_Alloc(script);
531 return qtrue;
532 }
533
534 if (token.string[1] != '\0') {
535 Q_strcat(script, 1024, va("\"%s\"", token.string));
536 } else {
537 Q_strcat(script, 1024, token.string);
538 }
539 Q_strcat(script, 1024, " ");
540 }
541 return qfalse;
542}

585void Fade(int *flags, float *f, float clamp, int *nextTime, int offsetTime, qboolean bFlags, float fadeAmount) {
586 if (*flags & (WINDOW_FADINGOUT | WINDOW_FADINGIN)) {
587 if (DC->realTime > *nextTime) {
588 *nextTime = DC->realTime + offsetTime;
589 if (*flags & WINDOW_FADINGOUT) {
590 *f -= fadeAmount;
591 if (bFlags && *f <= 0.0) {
592 *flags &= ~(WINDOW_FADINGOUT | WINDOW_VISIBLE);
593 }
594 } else {
595 *f += fadeAmount;
596 if (*f >= clamp) {
597 *f = clamp;
598 if (bFlags) {
599 *flags &= ~WINDOW_FADINGIN;
600 }
601 }
602 }
603 }
604 }
605}

609void Window_Paint(Window *w, float fadeAmount, float fadeClamp, float fadeCycle) {
610 //float bordersize = 0;
611 vec4_t color = {0};
612 rectDef_t fillRect;
613
614 if ( w == NULL ) {
615 return;
616 }
617
618 if (debugMode) {
619 color[0] = color[1] = color[2] = color[3] = 1;
620 DC->drawRect(w->rect.x, w->rect.y, w->rect.w, w->rect.h, 1, color);
621 }
622
623 if (w->style == 0 && w->border == 0) {
624 return;
625 }
626
627 fillRect = w->rect;
628
629 if (w->border != 0) {
630 fillRect.x += w->borderSize;
631 fillRect.y += w->borderSize;
632 fillRect.w -= w->borderSize + 1;
633 fillRect.h -= w->borderSize + 1;
634 }
635
636 if (w->style == WINDOW_STYLE_FILLED) {
637 // box, but possible a shader that needs filled
638 if (w->background) {
639 Fade(&w->flags, &w->backColor[3], fadeClamp, &w->nextTime, fadeCycle, qtrue, fadeAmount);
640 DC->setColor(w->backColor);
641 DC->drawHandlePic(fillRect.x, fillRect.y, fillRect.w, fillRect.h, w->background);
642 DC->setColor(NULL);
643 } else {
644 DC->fillRect(fillRect.x, fillRect.y, fillRect.w, fillRect.h, w->backColor);
645 }
646 } else if (w->style == WINDOW_STYLE_GRADIENT) {
647 GradientBar_Paint(&fillRect, w->backColor);
648 // gradient bar
649 } else if (w->style == WINDOW_STYLE_SHADER) {
650 if (w->flags & WINDOW_FORECOLORSET) {
651 DC->setColor(w->foreColor);
652 }
653 DC->drawHandlePic(fillRect.x, fillRect.y, fillRect.w, fillRect.h, w->background);
654 DC->setColor(NULL);
655 } else if (w->style == WINDOW_STYLE_TEAMCOLOR) {
656 if (DC->getTeamColor) {
657 DC->getTeamColor(&color);
658 DC->fillRect(fillRect.x, fillRect.y, fillRect.w, fillRect.h, color);
659 }
660 } else if (w->style == WINDOW_STYLE_CINEMATIC) {
661 if (w->cinematic == -1) {
662 w->cinematic = DC->playCinematic(w->cinematicName, fillRect.x, fillRect.y, fillRect.w, fillRect.h);
663 if (w->cinematic == -1) {
664 w->cinematic = -2;
665 }
666 }
667 if (w->cinematic >= 0) {
668 DC->runCinematicFrame(w->cinematic);
669 DC->drawCinematic(w->cinematic, fillRect.x, fillRect.y, fillRect.w, fillRect.h);
670 }
671 }
672
673 if (w->border == WINDOW_BORDER_FULL) {
674 // full
675 // HACK HACK HACK
676 if (w->style == WINDOW_STYLE_TEAMCOLOR) {
677 if (color[0] > 0) {
678 // red
679 color[0] = 1;
680 color[1] = color[2] = .5;
681
682 } else {
683 color[2] = 1;
684 color[0] = color[1] = .5;
685 }
686 color[3] = 1;
687 DC->drawRect(w->rect.x, w->rect.y, w->rect.w, w->rect.h, w->borderSize, color);
688 } else {
689 DC->drawRect(w->rect.x, w->rect.y, w->rect.w, w->rect.h, w->borderSize, w->borderColor);
690 }
691 } else if (w->border == WINDOW_BORDER_HORZ) {
692 // top/bottom
693 DC->setColor(w->borderColor);
694 DC->drawTopBottom(w->rect.x, w->rect.y, w->rect.w, w->rect.h, w->borderSize);
695 DC->setColor( NULL );
696 } else if (w->border == WINDOW_BORDER_VERT) {
697 // left right
698 DC->setColor(w->borderColor);
699 DC->drawSides(w->rect.x, w->rect.y, w->rect.w, w->rect.h, w->borderSize);
700 DC->setColor( NULL );
701 } else if (w->border == WINDOW_BORDER_KCGRADIENT) {
702 // this is just two gradient bars along each horz edge
703 rectDef_t r = w->rect;
704 r.h = w->borderSize;
705 GradientBar_Paint(&r, w->borderColor);
706 r.y = w->rect.y + w->rect.h - 1;
707 GradientBar_Paint(&r, w->borderColor);
708 }
709
710}

713void Item_SetScreenCoords(itemDef_t *item, float x, float y) {
714
715 if (item == NULL) {
716 return;
717 }
718
719 if (item->window.border != 0) {
720 x += item->window.borderSize;
721 y += item->window.borderSize;
722 }
723
724 item->window.rect.x = x + item->window.rectClient.x;
725 item->window.rect.y = y + item->window.rectClient.y;
726 item->window.rect.w = item->window.rectClient.w;
727 item->window.rect.h = item->window.rectClient.h;
728
729 // force the text rects to recompute
730 item->textRect.w = 0;
731 item->textRect.h = 0;
732}

734// FIXME: consolidate this with nearby stuff
735void Item_UpdatePosition(itemDef_t *item) {
736 float x, y;
737 menuDef_t *menu;
738
739 if (item == NULL || item->parent == NULL) {
740 return;
741 }
742
743 menu = item->parent;
744
745 x = menu->window.rect.x;
746 y = menu->window.rect.y;
747
748 if (menu->window.border != 0) {
749 x += menu->window.borderSize;
750 y += menu->window.borderSize;
751 }
752
753 Item_SetScreenCoords(item, x, y);
754
755}

757// menus
758void Menu_UpdatePosition(menuDef_t *menu) {
759 int i;
760 float x, y;
761
762 if (menu == NULL) {
763 return;
764 }
765
766 x = menu->window.rect.x;
767 y = menu->window.rect.y;
768 if (menu->window.border != 0) {
769 x += menu->window.borderSize;
770 y += menu->window.borderSize;
771 }
772
773 for (i = 0; i < menu->itemCount; i++) {
774 Item_SetScreenCoords(menu->items[i], x, y);
775 }
776}

780 return;

784 menu->window.rect.y = 0;

787 }
788 Menu_UpdatePosition(menu);
789}

791itemDef_t *Menu_ClearFocus(menuDef_t *menu) {
792 int i;
793 itemDef_t *ret = NULL;
794
795 if (menu == NULL) {
796 return NULL;
797 }
798
799 for (i = 0; i < menu->itemCount; i++) {
800 if (menu->items[i]->window.flags & WINDOW_HASFOCUS) {
801 ret = menu->items[i];
802 }
803 menu->items[i]->window.flags &= ~WINDOW_HASFOCUS;
804 if (menu->items[i]->leaveFocus) {
805 Item_RunScript(menu->items[i], menu->items[i]->leaveFocus);
806 }
807 }
808
809 return ret;
810}

825int Menu_ItemsMatchingGroup(menuDef_t *menu, const char *name) {
826 int i;
827 int count = 0;
828 for (i = 0; i < menu->itemCount; i++) {
829 if (Q_stricmp(menu->items[i]->window.name, name) == 0 || (menu->items[i]->window.group && Q_stricmp(menu->items[i]->window.group, name) == 0)) {
830 count++;
831 }
832 }
833 return count;
834}
835
836itemDef_t *Menu_GetMatchingItemByNumber(menuDef_t *menu, int index, const char *name) {
837 int i;
838 int count = 0;
839 for (i = 0; i < menu->itemCount; i++) {

1258 {"setteamcolor", &Script_SetTeamColor}, // sets this background color to team color
1259 {"setfocus", &Script_SetFocus}, // sets this background color to team color
1260 {"setplayermodel", &Script_SetPlayerModel}, // sets this background color to team color
1261 {"setplayerhead", &Script_SetPlayerHead}, // sets this background color to team color

1266 {"playlooped", &Script_playLooped}, // group/name
1267 {"orbit", &Script_Orbit} // group/name
1268};
1269
1270int scriptCommandCount = ARRAY_LEN(commandList);
1271
1272
1273void Item_RunScript(itemDef_t *item, const char *s) {
1274 char script[1024], *p;
1275 int i;
1276 qboolean bRan;
1277 memset(script, 0, sizeof(script));
1278 if (item && s && s[0]) {
1279 Q_strcat(script, 1024, s);
1280 p = script;
1281 while (1) {
1282 const char *command;
1283 // expect command then arguments, ; ends command, NULL ends script
1284 if (!String_Parse(&p, &command)) {
1285 return;
1286 }
1287
1288 if (command[0] == ';' && command[1] == '\0') {
1289 continue;
1290 }
1291
1292 bRan = qfalse;
1293 for (i = 0; i < scriptCommandCount; i++) {
1294 if (Q_stricmp(command, commandList[i].name) == 0) {
1295 (commandList[i].handler(item, &p));
1296 bRan = qtrue;
1297 break;
1298 }
1299 }
1300 // not in our auto list, pass to handler
1301 if (!bRan) {
1302 DC->runScript(&p);
1303 }
1304 }
1305 }
1306}
1307
1308
1309qboolean Item_EnableShowViaCvar(itemDef_t *item, int flag) {
1310 char script[1024], *p;
1311 memset(script, 0, sizeof(script));
1312 if (item && item->enableCvar && *item->enableCvar && item->cvarTest && *item->cvarTest) {
1313 char buff[1024];
1314 DC->getCVarString(item->cvarTest, buff, sizeof(buff));
1315
1316 Q_strcat(script, 1024, item->enableCvar);
1317 p = script;
1318 while (1) {
1319 const char *val;
1320 // expect value then ; or NULL, NULL ends list
1321 if (!String_Parse(&p, &val)) {
1322 return (item->cvarFlags & flag) ? qfalse : qtrue;
1323 }
1324
1325 if (val[0] == ';' && val[1] == '\0') {
1326 continue;
1327 }
1328
1329 // enable it if any of the values are true
1330 if (item->cvarFlags & flag) {
1331 if (Q_stricmp(buff, val) == 0) {
1332 return qtrue;
1333 }
1334 } else {
1335 // disable it if any of the values are true
1336 if (Q_stricmp(buff, val) == 0) {
1337 return qfalse;
1338 }
1339 }
1340
1341 }
1342 return (item->cvarFlags & flag) ? qfalse : qtrue;
1343 }
1344 return qtrue;
1345}

1347
1348// will optionaly set focus to this item
1349qboolean Item_SetFocus(itemDef_t *item, float x, float y) {
1350 int i;
1351 itemDef_t *oldFocus;
1352 sfxHandle_t *sfx = &DC->Assets.itemFocusSound;
1353 qboolean playSound = qfalse;
1354 menuDef_t *parent;
1355 // sanity check, non-null, not a decoration and does not already have the focus
1356 if (item == NULL || item->window.flags & WINDOW_DECORATION || item->window.flags & WINDOW_HASFOCUS || !(item->window.flags & WINDOW_VISIBLE)) {
1357 return qfalse;
1358 }
1359
1360 // this can be NULL
1361 parent = (menuDef_t*)item->parent;
1362
1363 // items can be enabled and disabled based on cvars
1364 if (item->cvarFlags & (CVAR_ENABLE | CVAR_DISABLE) && !Item_EnableShowViaCvar(item, CVAR_ENABLE)) {
1365 return qfalse;
1366 }
1367
1368 if (item->cvarFlags & (CVAR_SHOW | CVAR_HIDE) && !Item_EnableShowViaCvar(item, CVAR_SHOW)) {
1369 return qfalse;
1370 }
1371
1372 oldFocus = Menu_ClearFocus(item->parent);
1373
1374 if (item->type == ITEM_TYPE_TEXT) {
1375 rectDef_t r;
1376 r = item->textRect;
1377 r.y -= r.h;
1378 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1379 item->window.flags |= WINDOW_HASFOCUS;
1380 if (item->focusSound) {
1381 sfx = &item->focusSound;
1382 }
1383 playSound = qtrue;
1384 } else {
1385 if (oldFocus) {
1386 oldFocus->window.flags |= WINDOW_HASFOCUS;
1387 if (oldFocus->onFocus) {
1388 Item_RunScript(oldFocus, oldFocus->onFocus);
1389 }
1390 }
1391 }
1392 } else {
1393 item->window.flags |= WINDOW_HASFOCUS;
1394 if (item->onFocus) {
1395 Item_RunScript(item, item->onFocus);
1396 }
1397 if (item->focusSound) {
1398 sfx = &item->focusSound;
1399 }
1400 playSound = qtrue;
1401 }
1402
1403 if (playSound && sfx) {
1404 DC->startLocalSound( *sfx, CHAN_LOCAL_SOUND );
1405 }
1406
1407 for (i = 0; i < parent->itemCount; i++) {
1408 if (parent->items[i] == item) {
1409 parent->cursorItem = i;
1410 break;
1411 }
1412 }
1413
1414 return qtrue;
1415}

1434int Item_ListBox_ThumbPosition(itemDef_t *item) {
1435 float max, pos, size;

1437
1438 max = Item_ListBox_MaxScroll(item);
1439 if (item->window.flags & WINDOW_HORIZONTAL) {
1440 size = item->window.rect.w - (SCROLLBAR_SIZE * 2) - 2;
1441 if (max > 0) {
1442 pos = (size-SCROLLBAR_SIZE) / (float) max;
1443 } else {
1444 pos = 0;
1445 }
1446 pos *= listPtr->startPos;
1447 return item->window.rect.x + 1 + SCROLLBAR_SIZE + pos;
1448 }
1449 else {
1450 size = item->window.rect.h - (SCROLLBAR_SIZE * 2) - 2;
1451 if (max > 0) {
1452 pos = (size-SCROLLBAR_SIZE) / (float) max;
1453 } else {
1454 pos = 0;
1455 }
1456 pos *= listPtr->startPos;
1457 return item->window.rect.y + 1 + SCROLLBAR_SIZE + pos;
1458 }
1459}

1490
1491float Item_Slider_ThumbPosition(itemDef_t *item) {
1492 float value, range, x;
1493 editFieldDef_t *editDef = item->typeData;
1494
1495 if (item->text) {
1496 x = item->textRect.x + item->textRect.w + 8;
1497 } else {
1498 x = item->window.rect.x;
1499 }
1500
1501 if (!editDef || !item->cvar) {
1502 return x;
1503 }
1504
1505 value = DC->getCVarValue(item->cvar);
1506
1507 if (value < editDef->minVal) {
1508 value = editDef->minVal;
1509 } else if (value > editDef->maxVal) {
1510 value = editDef->maxVal;
1511 }
1512
1513 range = editDef->maxVal - editDef->minVal;
1514 value -= editDef->minVal;
1515 value /= range;
1516 //value /= (editDef->maxVal - editDef->minVal);
1517 value *= SLIDER_WIDTH;

1538int Item_ListBox_OverLB(itemDef_t *item, float x, float y) {
1539 rectDef_t r;
1540 int thumbstart;
1541
1542 if (item->window.flags & WINDOW_HORIZONTAL) {
1543 // check if on left arrow
1544 r.x = item->window.rect.x;
1545 r.y = item->window.rect.y + item->window.rect.h - SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1546 r.h = r.w = SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1547 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1548 return WINDOW_LB_LEFTARROW;
1549 }
1550 // check if on right arrow
1551 r.x = item->window.rect.x + item->window.rect.w - SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1552 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1553 return WINDOW_LB_RIGHTARROW;
1554 }
1555 // check if on thumb
1556 thumbstart = Item_ListBox_ThumbPosition(item);
1557 r.x = thumbstart;
1558 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1559 return WINDOW_LB_THUMB;
1560 }
1561 r.x = item->window.rect.x + SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1562 r.w = thumbstart - r.x;
1563 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1564 return WINDOW_LB_PGUP;
1565 }
1566 r.x = thumbstart + SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1567 r.w = item->window.rect.x + item->window.rect.w - SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1568 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1569 return WINDOW_LB_PGDN;
1570 }
1571 } else {
1572 r.x = item->window.rect.x + item->window.rect.w - SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1573 r.y = item->window.rect.y;
1574 r.h = r.w = SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1575 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1576 return WINDOW_LB_LEFTARROW;
1577 }
1578 r.y = item->window.rect.y + item->window.rect.h - SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1579 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1580 return WINDOW_LB_RIGHTARROW;
1581 }
1582 thumbstart = Item_ListBox_ThumbPosition(item);
1583 r.y = thumbstart;
1584 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1585 return WINDOW_LB_THUMB;
1586 }
1587 r.y = item->window.rect.y + SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1588 r.h = thumbstart - r.y;
1589 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1590 return WINDOW_LB_PGUP;
1591 }
1592 r.y = thumbstart + SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1593 r.h = item->window.rect.y + item->window.rect.h - SCROLLBAR_SIZE;
1594 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1595 return WINDOW_LB_PGDN;
1596 }
1597 }

1625 // text hit..

1642void Item_MouseEnter(itemDef_t *item, float x, float y) {
1643 rectDef_t r;
1644 if (item) {
1645 r = item->textRect;
1646 r.y -= r.h;
1647 // in the text rect?
1648
1649 // items can be enabled and disabled based on cvars
1650 if (item->cvarFlags & (CVAR_ENABLE | CVAR_DISABLE) && !Item_EnableShowViaCvar(item, CVAR_ENABLE)) {
1651 return;
1652 }
1653
1654 if (item->cvarFlags & (CVAR_SHOW | CVAR_HIDE) && !Item_EnableShowViaCvar(item, CVAR_SHOW)) {
1655 return;
1656 }
1657
1658 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&r, x, y)) {
1659 if (!(item->window.flags & WINDOW_MOUSEOVERTEXT)) {
1660 Item_RunScript(item, item->mouseEnterText);
1661 item->window.flags |= WINDOW_MOUSEOVERTEXT;
1662 }
1663 if (!(item->window.flags & WINDOW_MOUSEOVER)) {
1664 Item_RunScript(item, item->mouseEnter);
1665 item->window.flags |= WINDOW_MOUSEOVER;
1666 }
1667
1668 } else {
1669 // not in the text rect
1670 if (item->window.flags & WINDOW_MOUSEOVERTEXT) {
1671 // if we were
1672 Item_RunScript(item, item->mouseExitText);
1673 item->window.flags &= ~WINDOW_MOUSEOVERTEXT;
1674 }
1675 if (!(item->window.flags & WINDOW_MOUSEOVER)) {
1676 Item_RunScript(item, item->mouseEnter);
1677 item->window.flags |= WINDOW_MOUSEOVER;
1678 }
1679
1680 if (item->type == ITEM_TYPE_LISTBOX) {
1681 Item_ListBox_MouseEnter(item, x, y);
1682 }
1683 }
1684 }

1726qboolean Item_ListBox_HandleKey(itemDef_t *item, int key, qboolean down, qboolean force) {
1727 listBoxDef_t *listPtr = (listBoxDef_t*)item->typeData;
1728 int count = DC->feederCount(item->special);
1729 int max, viewmax;
1730
1731 if (force || (Rect_ContainsPoint(&item->window.rect, DC->cursorx, DC->cursory) && item->window.flags & WINDOW_HASFOCUS)) {
1732 max = Item_ListBox_MaxScroll(item);
1733 if (item->window.flags & WINDOW_HORIZONTAL) {
1734 viewmax = (item->window.rect.w / listPtr->elementWidth);
1735 if ( key == K_LEFTARROW || key == K_KP_LEFTARROW )
1736 {
1737 if (!listPtr->notselectable) {
1738 listPtr->cursorPos--;
1739 if (listPtr->cursorPos < 0) {
1740 listPtr->cursorPos = 0;
1741 }
1742 if (listPtr->cursorPos < listPtr->startPos) {
1743 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1744 }
1745 if (listPtr->cursorPos >= listPtr->startPos + viewmax) {
1746 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos - viewmax + 1;
1747 }
1748 item->cursorPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1749 DC->feederSelection(item->special, item->cursorPos);
1750 }
1751 else {
1752 listPtr->startPos--;
1753 if (listPtr->startPos < 0)
1754 listPtr->startPos = 0;
1755 }
1756 return qtrue;
1757 }
1758 if ( key == K_RIGHTARROW || key == K_KP_RIGHTARROW )
1759 {
1760 if (!listPtr->notselectable) {
1761 listPtr->cursorPos++;
1762 if (listPtr->cursorPos < listPtr->startPos) {
1763 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1764 }
1765 if (listPtr->cursorPos >= count) {
1766 listPtr->cursorPos = count-1;
1767 }
1768 if (listPtr->cursorPos >= listPtr->startPos + viewmax) {
1769 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos - viewmax + 1;
1770 }
1771 item->cursorPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1772 DC->feederSelection(item->special, item->cursorPos);
1773 }
1774 else {
1775 listPtr->startPos++;
1776 if (listPtr->startPos >= count)
1777 listPtr->startPos = count-1;
1778 }
1779 return qtrue;
1780 }
1781 }
1782 else {
1783 viewmax = (item->window.rect.h / listPtr->elementHeight);
1784 if ( key == K_UPARROW || key == K_KP_UPARROW )
1785 {
1786 if (!listPtr->notselectable) {
1787 listPtr->cursorPos--;
1788 if (listPtr->cursorPos < 0) {
1789 listPtr->cursorPos = 0;
1790 }
1791 if (listPtr->cursorPos < listPtr->startPos) {
1792 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1793 }
1794 if (listPtr->cursorPos >= listPtr->startPos + viewmax) {
1795 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos - viewmax + 1;
1796 }
1797 item->cursorPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1798 DC->feederSelection(item->special, item->cursorPos);
1799 }
1800 else {
1801 listPtr->startPos--;
1802 if (listPtr->startPos < 0)
1803 listPtr->startPos = 0;
1804 }
1805 return qtrue;
1806 }
1807 if ( key == K_DOWNARROW || key == K_KP_DOWNARROW )
1808 {
1809 if (!listPtr->notselectable) {
1810 listPtr->cursorPos++;
1811 if (listPtr->cursorPos < listPtr->startPos) {
1812 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1813 }
1814 if (listPtr->cursorPos >= count) {
1815 listPtr->cursorPos = count-1;
1816 }
1817 if (listPtr->cursorPos >= listPtr->startPos + viewmax) {
1818 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos - viewmax + 1;
1819 }
1820 item->cursorPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1821 DC->feederSelection(item->special, item->cursorPos);
1822 }
1823 else {
1824 listPtr->startPos++;
1825 if (listPtr->startPos > max)
1826 listPtr->startPos = max;
1827 }
1828 return qtrue;
1829 }
1830 }
1831
1832 // Use mouse wheel in vertical and horizontal menus.
1833 // If scrolling 3 items would replace over half of the
1834 // displayed items, only scroll 1 item at a time.
1835 if ( key == K_MWHEELUP ) {
1836 int scroll = viewmax < 6 ? 1 : 3;
1837 listPtr->startPos -= scroll;
1838 if (listPtr->startPos < 0) {
1839 listPtr->startPos = 0;
1840 }
1841 return qtrue;
1842 }
1843 if ( key == K_MWHEELDOWN ) {
1844 int scroll = viewmax < 6 ? 1 : 3;
1845 listPtr->startPos += scroll;
1846 if (listPtr->startPos > max) {
1847 listPtr->startPos = max;
1848 }
1849 return qtrue;
1850 }
1851
1852 // mouse hit
1853 if (key == K_MOUSE1 || key == K_MOUSE2) {
1854 if (item->window.flags & WINDOW_LB_LEFTARROW) {
1855 listPtr->startPos--;
1856 if (listPtr->startPos < 0) {
1857 listPtr->startPos = 0;
1858 }
1859 } else if (item->window.flags & WINDOW_LB_RIGHTARROW) {
1860 // one down
1861 listPtr->startPos++;
1862 if (listPtr->startPos > max) {
1863 listPtr->startPos = max;
1864 }
1865 } else if (item->window.flags & WINDOW_LB_PGUP) {
1866 // page up
1867 listPtr->startPos -= viewmax;
1868 if (listPtr->startPos < 0) {
1869 listPtr->startPos = 0;
1870 }
1871 } else if (item->window.flags & WINDOW_LB_PGDN) {
1872 // page down
1873 listPtr->startPos += viewmax;
1874 if (listPtr->startPos > max) {
1875 listPtr->startPos = max;
1876 }
1877 } else if (item->window.flags & WINDOW_LB_THUMB) {
1878 // Display_SetCaptureItem(item);
1879 } else {
1880 // select an item
1881 if (DC->realTime < lastListBoxClickTime && listPtr->doubleClick) {
1882 Item_RunScript(item, listPtr->doubleClick);
1883 }
1884 lastListBoxClickTime = DC->realTime + DOUBLE_CLICK_DELAY;
1885 if (item->cursorPos != listPtr->cursorPos) {
1886 item->cursorPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1887 DC->feederSelection(item->special, item->cursorPos);
1888 }
1889 }
1890 return qtrue;
1891 }
1892 if ( key == K_HOME || key == K_KP_HOME) {
1893 // home
1894 listPtr->startPos = 0;
1895 return qtrue;
1896 }
1897 if ( key == K_END || key == K_KP_END) {
1898 // end
1899 listPtr->startPos = max;
1900 return qtrue;
1901 }
1902 if (key == K_PGUP || key == K_KP_PGUP ) {
1903 // page up
1904 if (!listPtr->notselectable) {
1905 listPtr->cursorPos -= viewmax;
1906 if (listPtr->cursorPos < 0) {
1907 listPtr->cursorPos = 0;
1908 }
1909 if (listPtr->cursorPos < listPtr->startPos) {
1910 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1911 }
1912 if (listPtr->cursorPos >= listPtr->startPos + viewmax) {
1913 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos - viewmax + 1;
1914 }
1915 item->cursorPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1916 DC->feederSelection(item->special, item->cursorPos);
1917 }
1918 else {
1919 listPtr->startPos -= viewmax;
1920 if (listPtr->startPos < 0) {
1921 listPtr->startPos = 0;
1922 }
1923 }
1924 return qtrue;
1925 }
1926 if ( key == K_PGDN || key == K_KP_PGDN ) {
1927 // page down
1928 if (!listPtr->notselectable) {
1929 listPtr->cursorPos += viewmax;
1930 if (listPtr->cursorPos < listPtr->startPos) {
1931 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1932 }
1933 if (listPtr->cursorPos >= count) {
1934 listPtr->cursorPos = count-1;
1935 }
1936 if (listPtr->cursorPos >= listPtr->startPos + viewmax) {
1937 listPtr->startPos = listPtr->cursorPos - viewmax + 1;
1938 }
1939 item->cursorPos = listPtr->cursorPos;
1940 DC->feederSelection(item->special, item->cursorPos);
1941 }
1942 else {
1943 listPtr->startPos += viewmax;
1944 if (listPtr->startPos > max) {
1945 listPtr->startPos = max;
1946 }
1947 }
1948 return qtrue;
1949 }
1950 }
1951 return qfalse;
1952}

1987 multiDef_t *multiPtr = (multiDef_t*)item->typeData;
1988 if (multiPtr) {

1990 DC->getCVarString(item->cvar, buff, sizeof(buff));
1991 } else {
1992 value = DC->getCVarValue(item->cvar);

1995 if (multiPtr->strDef) {
1996 if (Q_stricmp(buff, multiPtr->cvarStr[i]) == 0) {

2001 return i;
2002 }
2003 }
2004 }

2035qboolean Item_Multi_HandleKey(itemDef_t *item, int key) {
2036 multiDef_t *multiPtr = (multiDef_t*)item->typeData;
2037 if (multiPtr) {
2038 if (item->cvar) {
2039 int select = 0;
2040 if (key == K_MOUSE1 || key == K_MOUSE2 || key == K_MOUSE3) {
2041 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&item->window.rect, DC->cursorx, DC->cursory) && item->window.flags & WINDOW_HASFOCUS) {
2042 select = (key == K_MOUSE2) ? -1 : 1;
2043 }
2044 } else {
2045 select = UI_SelectForKey(key);
2046 }
2047 if (select != 0) {
2048 int current = Item_Multi_FindCvarByValue(item) + select;
2049 int max = Item_Multi_CountSettings(item);
2050 if ( current < 0 ) {
2051 current = max-1;
2052 } else if ( current >= max ) {
2053 current = 0;
2054 }
2055 if (multiPtr->strDef) {
2056 DC->setCVar(item->cvar, multiPtr->cvarStr[current]);
2057 } else {
2058 float value = multiPtr->cvarValue[current];
2059 if (((float)((int) value)) == value) {
2060 DC->setCVar(item->cvar, va("%i", (int) value ));
2061 }
2062 else {
2063 DC->setCVar(item->cvar, va("%f", value ));
2064 }
2065 }
2066 return qtrue;
2067 }
2068 }
2069 }
2070 return qfalse;

2072
2073qboolean Item_TextField_HandleKey(itemDef_t *item, int key) {
2074 char buff[1024];
2075 int len;
2076 itemDef_t *newItem = NULL;
2077 editFieldDef_t *editPtr = (editFieldDef_t*)item->typeData;
2078
2079 if (item->cvar) {
2080
2081 memset(buff, 0, sizeof(buff));
2082 DC->getCVarString(item->cvar, buff, sizeof(buff));
2083 len = strlen(buff);
2084 if (editPtr->maxChars && len > editPtr->maxChars) {
2085 len = editPtr->maxChars;
2086 }
2087 if ( key & K_CHAR_FLAG ) {
2088 key &= ~K_CHAR_FLAG;
2089
2090
2091 if (key == 'h' - 'a' + 1 ) { // ctrl-h is backspace
2092 if ( item->cursorPos > 0 ) {
2093 memmove( &buff[item->cursorPos - 1], &buff[item->cursorPos], len + 1 - item->cursorPos);
2094 item->cursorPos--;
2095 if (item->cursorPos < editPtr->paintOffset) {
2096 editPtr->paintOffset--;
2097 }
2098 }
2099 DC->setCVar(item->cvar, buff);
2100 return qtrue;
2101 }
2102
2103
2104 //
2105 // ignore any non printable chars
2106 //
2107 if ( key < 32 || !item->cvar) {
2108 return qtrue;
2109 }
2110
2111 if (item->type == ITEM_TYPE_NUMERICFIELD) {
2112 if (key < '0' || key > '9') {
2113 return qfalse;
2114 }
2115 }
2116
2117 if (!DC->getOverstrikeMode()) {
2118 if (( len == MAX_EDITFIELD - 1 ) || (editPtr->maxChars && len >= editPtr->maxChars)) {
2119 return qtrue;
2120 }
2121 memmove( &buff[item->cursorPos + 1], &buff[item->cursorPos], len + 1 - item->cursorPos );
2122 } else {
2123 if (editPtr->maxChars && item->cursorPos >= editPtr->maxChars) {
2124 return qtrue;
2125 }
2126 }
2127
2128 buff[item->cursorPos] = key;
2129
2130 DC->setCVar(item->cvar, buff);
2131
2132 if (item->cursorPos < len + 1) {
2133 item->cursorPos++;
2134 if (editPtr->maxPaintChars && item->cursorPos > editPtr->maxPaintChars) {
2135 editPtr->paintOffset++;
2136 }
2137 }
2138
2139 } else {
2140
2141 if ( key == K_DEL || key == K_KP_DEL ) {
2142 if ( item->cursorPos < len ) {
2143 memmove( buff + item->cursorPos, buff + item->cursorPos + 1, len - item->cursorPos);
2144 DC->setCVar(item->cvar, buff);
2145 }
2146 return qtrue;
2147 }
2148
2149 if ( key == K_RIGHTARROW || key == K_KP_RIGHTARROW )
2150 {
2151 if (editPtr->maxPaintChars && item->cursorPos >= editPtr->maxPaintChars && item->cursorPos < len) {
2152 item->cursorPos++;
2153 editPtr->paintOffset++;
2154 return qtrue;
2155 }
2156 if (item->cursorPos < len) {
2157 item->cursorPos++;
2158 }
2159 return qtrue;
2160 }
2161
2162 if ( key == K_LEFTARROW || key == K_KP_LEFTARROW )
2163 {
2164 if ( item->cursorPos > 0 ) {
2165 item->cursorPos--;
2166 }
2167 if (item->cursorPos < editPtr->paintOffset) {
2168 editPtr->paintOffset--;
2169 }
2170 return qtrue;
2171 }
2172
2173 if ( key == K_HOME || key == K_KP_HOME) {// || ( tolower(key) == 'a' && trap_Key_IsDown( K_CTRL ) ) ) {
2174 item->cursorPos = 0;
2175 editPtr->paintOffset = 0;
2176 return qtrue;
2177 }
2178
2179 if ( key == K_END || key == K_KP_END) {// ( tolower(key) == 'e' && trap_Key_IsDown( K_CTRL ) ) ) {
2180 item->cursorPos = len;
2181 if(item->cursorPos > editPtr->maxPaintChars) {
2182 editPtr->paintOffset = len - editPtr->maxPaintChars;
2183 }
2184 return qtrue;
2185 }
2186
2187 if ( key == K_INS || key == K_KP_INS ) {
2188 DC->setOverstrikeMode(!DC->getOverstrikeMode());
2189 return qtrue;
2190 }
2191 }
2192
2193 if (key == K_TAB || key == K_DOWNARROW || key == K_KP_DOWNARROW) {
2194 newItem = Menu_SetNextCursorItem(item->parent);
2195 if (newItem && (newItem->type == ITEM_TYPE_EDITFIELD || newItem->type == ITEM_TYPE_NUMERICFIELD)) {
2196 g_editItem = newItem;
2197 }
2198 }
2199
2200 if (key == K_UPARROW || key == K_KP_UPARROW) {
2201 newItem = Menu_SetPrevCursorItem(item->parent);
2202 if (newItem && (newItem->type == ITEM_TYPE_EDITFIELD || newItem->type == ITEM_TYPE_NUMERICFIELD)) {
2203 g_editItem = newItem;
2204 }
2205 }
2206
2207 if ( key == K_ENTER || key == K_KP_ENTER || key == K_ESCAPE) {
2208 return qfalse;
2209 }
2210
2211 return qtrue;
2212 }
2213 return qfalse;
2214
2215}

2372qboolean Item_Slider_HandleKey(itemDef_t *item, int key, qboolean down) {
2373 float x, value, width, work;
2374
2375 //DC->Print("slider handle key\n");
2376 if (item->cvar) {
2377 if (key == K_MOUSE1 || key == K_MOUSE2 || key == K_MOUSE3) {
2378 editFieldDef_t *editDef = item->typeData;
2379 if (editDef && Rect_ContainsPoint(&item->window.rect, DC->cursorx, DC->cursory) && item->window.flags & WINDOW_HASFOCUS) {
2380 rectDef_t testRect;
2381 width = SLIDER_WIDTH;
2382 if (item->text) {
2383 x = item->textRect.x + item->textRect.w + 8;
2384 } else {
2385 x = item->window.rect.x;
2386 }
2387
2388 testRect = item->window.rect;
2389 testRect.x = x;
2390 value = (float)SLIDER_THUMB_WIDTH / 2;
2391 testRect.x -= value;
2392 //DC->Print("slider x: %f\n", testRect.x);
2393 testRect.w = (SLIDER_WIDTH + (float)SLIDER_THUMB_WIDTH / 2);
2394 //DC->Print("slider w: %f\n", testRect.w);
2395 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&testRect, DC->cursorx, DC->cursory)) {
2396 work = DC->cursorx - x;
2397 value = work / width;
2398 value *= (editDef->maxVal - editDef->minVal);
2399 // vm fuckage
2400 // value = (((float)(DC->cursorx - x)/ SLIDER_WIDTH) * (editDef->maxVal - editDef->minVal));

2403 return qtrue;
2404 }
2405 }
2406 } else {
2407 int select = UI_SelectForKey(key);
2408 if (select != 0) {
2409 editFieldDef_t *editDef = item->typeData;
2410 if (editDef) {
2411 // 20 is number of steps
2412 value = DC->getCVarValue(item->cvar) + (((editDef->maxVal - editDef->minVal)/20) * select);
2413
2414 if (value < editDef->minVal)
2415 value = editDef->minVal;
2416 else if (value > editDef->maxVal)
2417 value = editDef->maxVal;
2418
2419 DC->setCVar(item->cvar, va("%f", value));
2420 return qtrue;
2421 }
2422 }
2423 }
2424 }
2425 DC->Print("slider handle key exit\n");

2500itemDef_t *Menu_SetPrevCursorItem(menuDef_t *menu) {
2501 qboolean wrapped = qfalse;
2502 int oldCursor = menu->cursorItem;
2503
2504 if (menu->cursorItem < 0) {
2505 menu->cursorItem = menu->itemCount-1;
2506 wrapped = qtrue;
2507 }
2508
2509 while (menu->cursorItem > -1) {
2510
2511 menu->cursorItem--;
2512 if (menu->cursorItem < 0 && !wrapped) {
2513 wrapped = qtrue;
2514 menu->cursorItem = menu->itemCount -1;
2515 }
2516
2517 if (Item_SetFocus(menu->items[menu->cursorItem], DC->cursorx, DC->cursory)) {
2518 Menu_HandleMouseMove(menu, menu->items[menu->cursorItem]->window.rect.x + 1, menu->items[menu->cursorItem]->window.rect.y + 1);
2519 return menu->items[menu->cursorItem];
2520 }
2521 }
2522 menu->cursorItem = oldCursor;
2523 return NULL;
2524
2525}
2526
2527itemDef_t *Menu_SetNextCursorItem(menuDef_t *menu) {
2528
2529 qboolean wrapped = qfalse;
2530 int oldCursor = menu->cursorItem;
2531
2532
2533 if (menu->cursorItem == -1) {
2534 menu->cursorItem = 0;
2535 wrapped = qtrue;
2536 }
2537
2538 while (menu->cursorItem < menu->itemCount) {
2539
2540 menu->cursorItem++;
2541 if (menu->cursorItem >= menu->itemCount && !wrapped) {
2542 wrapped = qtrue;
2543 menu->cursorItem = 0;
2544 }
2545 if (Item_SetFocus(menu->items[menu->cursorItem], DC->cursorx, DC->cursory)) {
2546 Menu_HandleMouseMove(menu, menu->items[menu->cursorItem]->window.rect.x + 1, menu->items[menu->cursorItem]->window.rect.y + 1);
2547 return menu->items[menu->cursorItem];
2548 }
2549
2550 }
2551
2552 menu->cursorItem = oldCursor;
2553 return NULL;
2554}

2611void Menus_HandleOOBClick(menuDef_t *menu, int key, qboolean down) {
2612 if (menu) {
2613 int i;
2614 // basically the behaviour we are looking for is if there are windows in the stack.. see if
2615 // the cursor is within any of them.. if not close them otherwise activate them and pass the
2616 // key on.. force a mouse move to activate focus and script stuff
2617 if (down && menu->window.flags & WINDOW_OOB_CLICK) {
2618 Menu_RunCloseScript(menu);
2619 menu->window.flags &= ~(WINDOW_HASFOCUS | WINDOW_VISIBLE);
2620 }
2621
2622 for (i = 0; i < menuCount; i++) {
2623 if (Menu_OverActiveItem(&Menus[i], DC->cursorx, DC->cursory)) {
2624 Menu_RunCloseScript(menu);
2625 menu->window.flags &= ~(WINDOW_HASFOCUS | WINDOW_VISIBLE);
2626 Menus_Activate(&Menus[i]);
2627 Menu_HandleMouseMove(&Menus[i], DC->cursorx, DC->cursory);
2628 Menu_HandleKey(&Menus[i], key, down);
2629 }
2630 }
2631
2632 if (Display_VisibleMenuCount() == 0) {
2633 if (DC->Pause) {
2634 DC->Pause(qfalse);
2635 }
2636 }
2637 Display_CloseCinematics();
2638 }
2639}

2653// menu item key horizontal action: -1 = previous value, 1 = next value, 0 = no change
2654int UI_SelectForKey(int key)
2655{
2656 switch (key) {
2657 case K_MOUSE1:
2658 case K_MOUSE3:
2659 case K_ENTER:
2660 case K_KP_ENTER:
2661 case K_RIGHTARROW:
2662 case K_KP_RIGHTARROW:
2663 case K_JOY1:
2664 case K_JOY2:
2665 case K_JOY3:
2666 case K_JOY4:
2667 return 1; // next
2668
2669 case K_MOUSE2:
2670 case K_LEFTARROW:
2671 case K_KP_LEFTARROW:
2672 return -1; // previous
2673 }
2674
2675 // no change
2676 return 0;
2677}

2679void Menu_HandleKey(menuDef_t *menu, int key, qboolean down) {
2680 int i;
2681 itemDef_t *item = NULL;
2682
2683 if (g_waitingForKey && down) {
2684 Item_Bind_HandleKey(g_bindItem, key, down);
2685 return;
2686 }
2687
2688 if (g_editingField && down) {
2689 if (!Item_TextField_HandleKey(g_editItem, key)) {
2690 g_editingField = qfalse;
2691 g_editItem = NULL;
2692 return;
2693 } else if (key == K_MOUSE1 || key == K_MOUSE2 || key == K_MOUSE3) {
2694 g_editingField = qfalse;
2695 g_editItem = NULL;
2696 Display_MouseMove(NULL, DC->cursorx, DC->cursory);
2697 } else if (key == K_TAB || key == K_UPARROW || key == K_DOWNARROW) {
2698 return;
2699 }
2700 }
2701
2702 if (menu == NULL) {
2703 return;
2704 }
2705
2706 // see if the mouse is within the window bounds and if so is this a mouse click
2707 if (down && !(menu->window.flags & WINDOW_POPUP) && !Rect_ContainsPoint(&menu->window.rect, DC->cursorx, DC->cursory)) {
2708 static qboolean inHandleKey = qfalse;
2709 if (!inHandleKey && ( key == K_MOUSE1 || key == K_MOUSE2 || key == K_MOUSE3 ) ) {
2710 inHandleKey = qtrue;
2711 Menus_HandleOOBClick(menu, key, down);
2712 inHandleKey = qfalse;
2713 return;
2714 }
2715 }
2716
2717 // get the item with focus
2718 for (i = 0; i < menu->itemCount; i++) {
2719 if (menu->items[i]->window.flags & WINDOW_HASFOCUS) {
2720 item = menu->items[i];
2721 }
2722 }
2723
2724 if (item != NULL) {
2725 if (Item_HandleKey(item, key, down)) {
2726 Item_Action(item);
2727 return;
2728 }
2729 }
2730
2731 if (!down) {
2732 return;
2733 }
2734
2735 // default handling
2736 switch ( key ) {
2737
2738 case K_F11:
2739 if (DC->getCVarValue("developer")) {
2740 debugMode ^= 1;
2741 }
2742 break;
2743
2744 case K_F12:
2745 if (DC->getCVarValue("developer")) {
2746 DC->executeText(EXEC_APPEND, "screenshot\n");
2747 }
2748 break;
2749 case K_KP_UPARROW:
2750 case K_UPARROW:
2751 Menu_SetPrevCursorItem(menu);
2752 break;
2753
2754 case K_ESCAPE:
2755 if (!g_waitingForKey && menu->onESC) {
2756 itemDef_t it;
2757 it.parent = menu;
2758 Item_RunScript(&it, menu->onESC);
2759 }
2760 break;
2761 case K_TAB:
2762 case K_KP_DOWNARROW:
2763 case K_DOWNARROW:
2764 Menu_SetNextCursorItem(menu);
2765 break;
2766
2767 case K_MOUSE1:
2768 case K_MOUSE2:
2769 if (item) {
2770 if (item->type == ITEM_TYPE_TEXT) {
2771 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(Item_CorrectedTextRect(item), DC->cursorx, DC->cursory)) {
2772 Item_Action(item);
2773 }
2774 } else if (item->type == ITEM_TYPE_EDITFIELD || item->type == ITEM_TYPE_NUMERICFIELD) {
2775 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&item->window.rect, DC->cursorx, DC->cursory)) {
2776 item->cursorPos = 0;
2777 g_editingField = qtrue;
2778 g_editItem = item;
2779 }
2780 } else {
2781 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&item->window.rect, DC->cursorx, DC->cursory)) {
2782 Item_Action(item);
2783 }
2784 }
2785 }
2786 break;
2787
2788 case K_JOY1:
2789 case K_JOY2:
2790 case K_JOY3:
2791 case K_JOY4:
2792 case K_AUX1:
2793 case K_AUX2:
2794 case K_AUX3:
2795 case K_AUX4:
2796 case K_AUX5:
2797 case K_AUX6:
2798 case K_AUX7:
2799 case K_AUX8:
2800 case K_AUX9:
2801 case K_AUX10:
2802 case K_AUX11:
2803 case K_AUX12:
2804 case K_AUX13:
2805 case K_AUX14:
2806 case K_AUX15:
2807 case K_AUX16:
2808 case K_KP_ENTER:
2809 case K_ENTER:
2810 if (item) {
2811 if (item->type == ITEM_TYPE_EDITFIELD || item->type == ITEM_TYPE_NUMERICFIELD) {
2812 item->cursorPos = 0;
2813 g_editingField = qtrue;
2814 g_editItem = item;
2815 } else {
2816 Item_Action(item);
2817 }
2818 }
2819 break;
2820 }
2821}

2836void Item_SetTextExtents(itemDef_t *item, int *width, int *height, const char *text) {
2837 const char *textPtr = (text) ? text : item->text;
2838
2839 if (textPtr == NULL ) {
2840 return;
2841 }
2842
2843 *width = item->textRect.w;
2844 *height = item->textRect.h;
2845
2846 // keeps us from computing the widths and heights more than once
2847 if (*width == 0 || (item->type == ITEM_TYPE_OWNERDRAW && item->textalignment == ITEM_ALIGN_CENTER)) {
2848 int originalWidth = DC->textWidth(item->text, item->textscale, 0);
2849
2850 if (item->type == ITEM_TYPE_OWNERDRAW && (item->textalignment == ITEM_ALIGN_CENTER || item->textalignment == ITEM_ALIGN_RIGHT)) {
2851 originalWidth += DC->ownerDrawWidth(item->window.ownerDraw, item->textscale);
2852 } else if (item->type == ITEM_TYPE_EDITFIELD && item->textalignment == ITEM_ALIGN_CENTER && item->cvar) {
2853 char buff[256];
2854 DC->getCVarString(item->cvar, buff, 256);
2855 originalWidth += DC->textWidth(buff, item->textscale, 0);
2856 }
2857
2858 *width = DC->textWidth(textPtr, item->textscale, 0);
2859 *height = DC->textHeight(textPtr, item->textscale, 0);
2860 item->textRect.w = *width;
2861 item->textRect.h = *height;
2862 item->textRect.x = item->textalignx;
2863 item->textRect.y = item->textaligny;
2864 if (item->textalignment == ITEM_ALIGN_RIGHT) {
2865 item->textRect.x = item->textalignx - originalWidth;
2866 } else if (item->textalignment == ITEM_ALIGN_CENTER) {
2867 item->textRect.x = item->textalignx - originalWidth / 2;
2868 }
2869
2870 ToWindowCoords(&item->textRect.x, &item->textRect.y, &item->window);
2871 }
2872}

2904void Item_Text_AutoWrapped_Paint(itemDef_t *item) {
2905 char text[1024];
2906 const char *p, *textPtr, *newLinePtr;
2907 char buff[1024];
2908 int width, height, len, textWidth, newLine, newLineWidth;
2909 float y;
2910 vec4_t color;
2911
2912 textWidth = 0;
2913 newLinePtr = NULL;
2914
2915 if (item->text == NULL) {
2916 if (item->cvar == NULL) {
2917 return;
2918 }
2919 else {
2920 DC->getCVarString(item->cvar, text, sizeof(text));
2921 textPtr = text;
2922 }
2923 }
2924 else {
2925 textPtr = item->text;
2926 }
2927 if (*textPtr == '\0') {
2928 return;
2929 }
2930 Item_TextColor(item, &color);
2931 Item_SetTextExtents(item, &width, &height, textPtr);
2932
2933 y = item->textaligny;
2934 len = 0;
2935 buff[0] = '\0';
2936 newLine = 0;
2937 newLineWidth = 0;
2938 p = textPtr;
2939 while (p) {
2940 if (*p == ' ' || *p == '\t' || *p == '\n' || *p == '\0') {
2941 newLine = len;
2942 newLinePtr = p+1;
2943 newLineWidth = textWidth;
2944 }
2945 textWidth = DC->textWidth(buff, item->textscale, 0);
2946 if ( (newLine && textWidth > item->window.rect.w) || *p == '\n' || *p == '\0') {
2947 if (len) {
2948 if (item->textalignment == ITEM_ALIGN_LEFT) {
2949 item->textRect.x = item->textalignx;
2950 } else if (item->textalignment == ITEM_ALIGN_RIGHT) {
2951 item->textRect.x = item->textalignx - newLineWidth;
2952 } else if (item->textalignment == ITEM_ALIGN_CENTER) {
2953 item->textRect.x = item->textalignx - newLineWidth / 2;
2954 }
2955 item->textRect.y = y;
2956 ToWindowCoords(&item->textRect.x, &item->textRect.y, &item->window);
2957 //
2958 buff[newLine] = '\0';
2959 DC->drawText(item->textRect.x, item->textRect.y, item->textscale, color, buff, 0, 0, item->textStyle);
2960 }
2961 if (*p == '\0') {
2962 break;
2963 }
2964 //
2965 y += height + 5;
2966 p = newLinePtr;
2967 len = 0;
2968 newLine = 0;
2969 newLineWidth = 0;
2970 continue;
2971 }
2972 buff[len++] = *p++;
2973 buff[len] = '\0';
2974 }
2975}

3514
3515qboolean Item_Bind_HandleKey(itemDef_t *item, int key, qboolean down) {
3516 int id;
3517 int i;
3518
3519 if (!g_waitingForKey)
3520 {
3521 if (down && ((key == K_MOUSE1 && Rect_ContainsPoint(&item->window.rect, DC->cursorx, DC->cursory))
3522 || key == K_ENTER || key == K_KP_ENTER || key == K_JOY1 || key == K_JOY2 || key == K_JOY3 || key == K_JOY4)) {
3523 g_waitingForKey = qtrue;
3524 g_bindItem = item;
3525 }
3526 return qtrue;
3527 }
3528 else
3529 {
3530 if (g_bindItem == NULL) {
3531 return qtrue;
3532 }
3533
3534 if (key & K_CHAR_FLAG) {
3535 return qtrue;
3536 }
3537
3538 switch (key)
3539 {
3540 case K_ESCAPE:
3541 g_waitingForKey = qfalse;
3542 return qtrue;
3543
3544 case K_BACKSPACE:
3545 id = BindingIDFromName(item->cvar);
3546 if (id != -1) {
3547 g_bindings[id].bind1 = -1;
3548 g_bindings[id].bind2 = -1;
3549 }
3550 Controls_SetConfig(qtrue);
3551 g_waitingForKey = qfalse;
3552 g_bindItem = NULL;
3553 return qtrue;
3554
3555 case '`':
3556 return qtrue;
3557 }
3558 }
3559
3560 if (key != -1)
3561 {
3562
3563 for (i=0; i < g_bindCount; i++)
3564 {
3565
3566 if (g_bindings[i].bind2 == key) {
3567 g_bindings[i].bind2 = -1;
3568 }
3569
3570 if (g_bindings[i].bind1 == key)
3571 {
3572 g_bindings[i].bind1 = g_bindings[i].bind2;
3573 g_bindings[i].bind2 = -1;
3574 }
3575 }
3576 }
3577
3578
3579 id = BindingIDFromName(item->cvar);
3580
3581 if (id != -1) {
3582 if (key == -1) {
3583 if( g_bindings[id].bind1 != -1 ) {
3584 DC->setBinding( g_bindings[id].bind1, "" );
3585 g_bindings[id].bind1 = -1;
3586 }
3587 if( g_bindings[id].bind2 != -1 ) {
3588 DC->setBinding( g_bindings[id].bind2, "" );
3589 g_bindings[id].bind2 = -1;
3590 }
3591 }
3592 else if (g_bindings[id].bind1 == -1) {
3593 g_bindings[id].bind1 = key;
3594 }
3595 else if (g_bindings[id].bind1 != key && g_bindings[id].bind2 == -1) {
3596 g_bindings[id].bind2 = key;
3597 }
3598 else {
3599 DC->setBinding( g_bindings[id].bind1, "" );
3600 DC->setBinding( g_bindings[id].bind2, "" );
3601 g_bindings[id].bind1 = key;
3602 g_bindings[id].bind2 = -1;
3603 }
3604 }
3605
3606 Controls_SetConfig(qtrue);
3607 g_waitingForKey = qfalse;
3608
3609 return qtrue;
3610}

3935 if (DC->realTime > item->window.nextTime) {
3936 float rx, ry, a, c, s, w, h;
3937
3938 item->window.nextTime = DC->realTime + item->window.offsetTime;
3939 // translate
3940 w = item->window.rectClient.w / 2;
3941 h = item->window.rectClient.h / 2;
3942 rx = item->window.rectClient.x + w - item->window.rectEffects.x;
3943 ry = item->window.rectClient.y + h - item->window.rectEffects.y;
3944 a = 3 * M_PI / 180;
3945 c = cos(a);
3946 s = sin(a);
3947 item->window.rectClient.x = (rx * c - ry * s) + item->window.rectEffects.x - w;
3948 item->window.rectClient.y = (rx * s + ry * c) + item->window.rectEffects.y - h;
3949 Item_UpdatePosition(item);
3950
3951 }
3952 }
3953
3954
3955 if (item->window.flags & WINDOW_INTRANSITION) {
3956 if (DC->realTime > item->window.nextTime) {
3957 int done = 0;
3958 item->window.nextTime = DC->realTime + item->window.offsetTime;
3959 // transition the x,y
3960 if (item->window.rectClient.x == item->window.rectEffects.x) {
3961 done++;
3962 } else {
3963 if (item->window.rectClient.x < item->window.rectEffects.x) {
3964 item->window.rectClient.x += item->window.rectEffects2.x;
3965 if (item->window.rectClient.x > item->window.rectEffects.x) {
3966 item->window.rectClient.x = item->window.rectEffects.x;
3967 done++;
3968 }
3969 } else {
3970 item->window.rectClient.x -= item->window.rectEffects2.x;
3971 if (item->window.rectClient.x < item->window.rectEffects.x) {
3972 item->window.rectClient.x = item->window.rectEffects.x;
3973 done++;
3974 }
3975 }
3976 }
3977 if (item->window.rectClient.y == item->window.rectEffects.y) {
3978 done++;
3979 } else {
3980 if (item->window.rectClient.y < item->window.rectEffects.y) {
3981 item->window.rectClient.y += item->window.rectEffects2.y;
3982 if (item->window.rectClient.y > item->window.rectEffects.y) {
3983 item->window.rectClient.y = item->window.rectEffects.y;
3984 done++;
3985 }
3986 } else {
3987 item->window.rectClient.y -= item->window.rectEffects2.y;
3988 if (item->window.rectClient.y < item->window.rectEffects.y) {
3989 item->window.rectClient.y = item->window.rectEffects.y;
3990 done++;
3991 }
3992 }
3993 }
3994 if (item->window.rectClient.w == item->window.rectEffects.w) {
3995 done++;
3996 } else {
3997 if (item->window.rectClient.w < item->window.rectEffects.w) {
3998 item->window.rectClient.w += item->window.rectEffects2.w;
3999 if (item->window.rectClient.w > item->window.rectEffects.w) {
4000 item->window.rectClient.w = item->window.rectEffects.w;

4229void Menu_HandleMouseMove(menuDef_t *menu, float x, float y) {
4230 int i, pass;
4231 qboolean focusSet = qfalse;
4232
4233 itemDef_t *overItem;
4234 if (menu == NULL) {
4235 return;
4236 }
4237
4238 if (!(menu->window.flags & (WINDOW_VISIBLE | WINDOW_FORCED))) {
4239 return;
4240 }
4241
4242 if (itemCapture) {
4243 //Item_MouseMove(itemCapture, x, y);
4244 return;
4245 }
4246
4247 if (g_waitingForKey || g_editingField) {
4248 return;
4249 }
4250
4251 // FIXME: this is the whole issue of focus vs. mouse over..
4252 // need a better overall solution as i don't like going through everything twice
4253 for (pass = 0; pass < 2; pass++) {
4254 for (i = 0; i < menu->itemCount; i++) {
4255 // turn off focus each item
4256 // menu->items[i].window.flags &= ~WINDOW_HASFOCUS;
4257
4258 if (!(menu->items[i]->window.flags & (WINDOW_VISIBLE | WINDOW_FORCED))) {
4259 continue;
4260 }
4261
4262 // items can be enabled and disabled based on cvars
4263 if (menu->items[i]->cvarFlags & (CVAR_ENABLE | CVAR_DISABLE) && !Item_EnableShowViaCvar(menu->items[i], CVAR_ENABLE)) {
4264 continue;
4265 }
4266
4267 if (menu->items[i]->cvarFlags & (CVAR_SHOW | CVAR_HIDE) && !Item_EnableShowViaCvar(menu->items[i], CVAR_SHOW)) {
4268 continue;
4269 }
4270
4271
4272
4273 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&menu->items[i]->window.rect, x, y)) {
4274 if (pass == 1) {
4275 overItem = menu->items[i];
4276 if (overItem->type == ITEM_TYPE_TEXT && overItem->text) {
4277 if (!Rect_ContainsPoint(Item_CorrectedTextRect(overItem), x, y)) {
4278 continue;
4279 }
4280 }
4281 // if we are over an item
4282 if (IsVisible(overItem->window.flags)) {
4283 // different one
4284 Item_MouseEnter(overItem, x, y);
4285 // Item_SetMouseOver(overItem, qtrue);
4286
4287 // if item is not a decoration see if it can take focus
4288 if (!focusSet) {
4289 focusSet = Item_SetFocus(overItem, x, y);
4290 }
4291 }
4292 }
4293 } else if (menu->items[i] && menu->items[i]->window.flags & WINDOW_MOUSEOVER) {
4294 Item_MouseLeave(menu->items[i]);
4295 Item_SetMouseOver(menu->items[i], qfalse);
4296 }
4297 }
4298 }

4374/*
4375===============
4376Keyword Hash
4377===============
4378*/
4379
4380#define KEYWORDHASH_SIZE 512
4381
4382typedef struct keywordHash_s
4383{
4384 char *keyword;
4385 qboolean (*func)(itemDef_t *item, int handle);
4386 struct keywordHash_s *next;
4387} keywordHash_t;
4388
4389int KeywordHash_Key(char *keyword) {
4390 int hash, i;
4391
4392 hash = 0;
4393 for (i = 0; keyword[i] != '\0'; i++) {
4394 if (keyword[i] >= 'A' && keyword[i] <= 'Z')
4395 hash += (keyword[i] + ('a' - 'A')) * (119 + i);
4396 else
4397 hash += keyword[i] * (119 + i);
4398 }
4399 hash = (hash ^ (hash >> 10) ^ (hash >> 20)) & (KEYWORDHASH_SIZE-1);
4400 return hash;
4401}
4402
4403void KeywordHash_Add(keywordHash_t *table[], keywordHash_t *key) {
4404 int hash;
4405
4406 hash = KeywordHash_Key(key->keyword);
4407/*
4408 if (table[hash]) {
4409 int collision = qtrue;
4410 }
4411*/
4412 key->next = table[hash];
4413 table[hash] = key;
4414}
4415
4416keywordHash_t *KeywordHash_Find(keywordHash_t *table[], char *keyword)
4417{
4418 keywordHash_t *key;
4419 int hash;
4420
4421 hash = KeywordHash_Key(keyword);
4422 for (key = table[hash]; key; key = key->next) {
4423 if (!Q_stricmp(key->keyword, keyword))
4424 return key;
4425 }
4426 return NULL;
4427}

4986qboolean ItemParse_cvarStrList( itemDef_t *item, int handle ) {
4987 pc_token_t token;
4988 multiDef_t *multiPtr;
4989 int pass;
4990
4991 Item_ValidateTypeData(item);
4992 if (!item->typeData)
4993 return qfalse;
4994 multiPtr = (multiDef_t*)item->typeData;
4995 multiPtr->count = 0;
4996 multiPtr->strDef = qtrue;
4997
4998 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
4999 return qfalse;
5000 if (*token.string != '{') {
5001 return qfalse;
5002 }
5003
5004 pass = 0;
5005 while ( 1 ) {
5006 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token)) {
5007 PC_SourceError(handle, "end of file inside menu item");
5008 return qfalse;
5009 }
5010
5011 if (*token.string == '}') {
5012 return qtrue;
5013 }
5014
5015 if (*token.string == ',' || *token.string == ';') {
5016 continue;
5017 }
5018
5019 if (pass == 0) {
5020 multiPtr->cvarList[multiPtr->count] = String_Alloc(token.string);
5021 pass = 1;
5022 } else {
5023 multiPtr->cvarStr[multiPtr->count] = String_Alloc(token.string);
5024 pass = 0;
5025 multiPtr->count++;
5026 if (multiPtr->count >= MAX_MULTI_CVARS) {
5027 return qfalse;
5028 }
5029 }
5030
5031 }
5032 return qfalse;
5033}

5036 pc_token_t token;
5037 multiDef_t *multiPtr;
5038
5039 Item_ValidateTypeData(item);
5040 if (!item->typeData)
5041 return qfalse;
5042 multiPtr = (multiDef_t*)item->typeData;
5043 multiPtr->count = 0;

5045
5046 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
5047 return qfalse;
5048 if (*token.string != '{') {
5049 return qfalse;

5051
5052 while ( 1 ) {
5053 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token)) {
5054 PC_SourceError(handle, "end of file inside menu item");
5055 return qfalse;
5056 }
5057
5058 if (*token.string == '}') {
5059 return qtrue;

5221/*
5222===============
5223Item_ApplyHacks
5224
5225Hacks to fix issues with Team Arena menu scripts
5226===============
5227*/
5228static void Item_ApplyHacks( itemDef_t *item ) {
5229
5230 // Fix length of favorite address in createfavorite.menu
5231 if ( item->type == ITEM_TYPE_EDITFIELD && item->cvar && !Q_stricmp( item->cvar, "ui_favoriteAddress" ) ) {
5232 editFieldDef_t *editField = (editFieldDef_t *)item->typeData;
5233
5234 // enough to hold an IPv6 address plus null
5235 if ( editField->maxChars < 48 ) {
5236 Com_Printf( "Extended create favorite address edit field length to hold an IPv6 address\n" );
5237 editField->maxChars = 48;
5238 }
5239 }
5240
5241 if ( item->type == ITEM_TYPE_EDITFIELD && item->cvar && ( !Q_stricmp( item->cvar, "ui_Name" ) || !Q_stricmp( item->cvar, "ui_findplayer" ) ) ) {
5242 editFieldDef_t *editField = (editFieldDef_t *)item->typeData;
5243
5244 // enough to hold a full player name
5245 if ( editField->maxChars < MAX_NAME_LENGTH ) {
5246 if ( editField->maxPaintChars > editField->maxChars ) {
5247 editField->maxPaintChars = editField->maxChars;
5248 }
5249
5250 Com_Printf( "Extended player name field using cvar %s to %d characters\n", item->cvar, MAX_NAME_LENGTH );
5251 editField->maxChars = MAX_NAME_LENGTH;
5252 }
5253 }
5254
5255}
5256
5257/*
5258===============
5259Item_Parse
5260===============
5261*/
5262qboolean Item_Parse(int handle, itemDef_t *item) {
5263 pc_token_t token;
5264 keywordHash_t *key;
5265
5266
5267 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
5268 return qfalse;
5269 if (*token.string != '{') {
5270 return qfalse;
5271 }
5272 while ( 1 ) {
5273 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token)) {
5274 PC_SourceError(handle, "end of file inside menu item");
5275 return qfalse;
5276 }
5277
5278 if (*token.string == '}') {
5279 Item_ApplyHacks( item );
5280 return qtrue;
5281 }
5282
5283 key = KeywordHash_Find(itemParseKeywordHash, token.string);
5284 if (!key) {
5285 PC_SourceError(handle, "unknown menu item keyword %s", token.string);
5286 continue;
5287 }
5288 if ( !key->func(item, handle) ) {
5289 PC_SourceError(handle, "couldn't parse menu item keyword %s", token.string);
5290 return qfalse;
5291 }
5292 }
5293 return qfalse;
5294}

5653keywordHash_t *menuParseKeywordHash[KEYWORDHASH_SIZE];
5654
5655/*
5656===============
5657Menu_SetupKeywordHash
5658===============
5659*/
5660void Menu_SetupKeywordHash(void) {
5661 int i;
5662
5663 memset(menuParseKeywordHash, 0, sizeof(menuParseKeywordHash));
5664 for (i = 0; menuParseKeywords[i].keyword; i++) {
5665 KeywordHash_Add(menuParseKeywordHash, &menuParseKeywords[i]);
5666 }
5667}
5668
5669/*
5670===============
5671Menu_Parse
5672===============
5673*/
5674qboolean Menu_Parse(int handle, menuDef_t *menu) {
5675 pc_token_t token;
5676 keywordHash_t *key;
5677
5678 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
5679 return qfalse;
5680 if (*token.string != '{') {
5681 return qfalse;
5682 }
5683
5684 while ( 1 ) {
5685
5686 memset(&token, 0, sizeof(pc_token_t));
5687 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token)) {
5688 PC_SourceError(handle, "end of file inside menu");
5689 return qfalse;
5690 }
5691
5692 if (*token.string == '}') {
5693 return qtrue;
5694 }
5695
5696 key = KeywordHash_Find(menuParseKeywordHash, token.string);
5697 if (!key) {
5698 PC_SourceError(handle, "unknown menu keyword %s", token.string);
5699 continue;
5700 }
5701 if ( !key->func((itemDef_t*)menu, handle) ) {
5702 PC_SourceError(handle, "couldn't parse menu keyword %s", token.string);
5703 return qfalse;
5704 }
5705 }
5706 return qfalse;
5707}

5863static qboolean Menu_OverActiveItem(menuDef_t *menu, float x, float y) {
5864 if (menu && menu->window.flags & (WINDOW_VISIBLE | WINDOW_FORCED)) {
5865 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&menu->window.rect, x, y)) {
5866 int i;
5867 for (i = 0; i < menu->itemCount; i++) {
5868 // turn off focus each item
5869 // menu->items[i].window.flags &= ~WINDOW_HASFOCUS;
5870
5871 if (!(menu->items[i]->window.flags & (WINDOW_VISIBLE | WINDOW_FORCED))) {
5872 continue;
5873 }
5874
5875 if (menu->items[i]->window.flags & WINDOW_DECORATION) {
5876 continue;
5877 }
5878
5879 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(&menu->items[i]->window.rect, x, y)) {
5880 itemDef_t *overItem = menu->items[i];
5881 if (overItem->type == ITEM_TYPE_TEXT && overItem->text) {
5882 if (Rect_ContainsPoint(Item_CorrectedTextRect(overItem), x, y)) {
5883 return qtrue;
5884 } else {
5885 continue;
5886 }
5887 } else {
5888 return qtrue;
5889 }
5890 }
5891 }
5892
5893 }
5894 }
5895 return qfalse;
5896}
